
- Classes: `Customer`, `Product`, `Order`, `OrderLine`, `Stock`, `Delivery`, `Invoice`
- Relationships: associations, aggregations, and compositions
- Attributes and methods where necessary
- Constraints and notes based on system behavior

---

@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -vatNumber: String
  +register(): void
}

class Product {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
  -stockLevel: int
  +updateStock(newLevel: int): void
}

class Order {
  -id: int
  -customer: Customer
  -orderLines: List<OrderLine>
  -isPaid: boolean
  -isFullyShipped: boolean
  -invoice: Invoice
  +placeOrder(): void
  +markAsPaid(): void
  +markAsFullyShipped(): void
}

class OrderLine {
  -id: int
  -product: Product
  -quantity: int
  -isShipped: boolean
  +ship(): void
}

class Stock {
  -products: Map<Product, Integer>
  +adjustStock(product: Product, quantity: int): void
}

class Delivery {
  -id: int
  -orderLines: List<OrderLine>
  -status: String (Packed | Shipped | Received | Damaged)
  -deliveryAddress: String
  +pack(): void
  +ship(): void
  +receive(): void
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -order: Order
  -amount: double
  -dueDate: Date
  -paymentStatus: String (Unpaid | Paid)
  +generate(): void
  +markAsPaid(): void
}

note right of Customer
  VAT number is required for tax purposes.
end note

note right of Order
  An order can be paid before or after delivery.
  It must be fully paid before being marked as shipped.
end note

note right of OrderLine
  Each line is tracked individually for shipment status.
end note

note right of Delivery
  A delivery may contain multiple order lines.
  Status transitions are tracked: Packed -> Shipped -> Received or Damaged.
end note

note right of Stock
  Adjusted manually at end of each working day.
end note

note right of Invoice
  Customers can choose to pay upon placing the order or after delivery.
end note

Customer "1" *-- "0..*" Order : places
Order "1" *-- "0..*" OrderLine : contains
OrderLine "1" --> "1" Product : refers to
Order "1" --> "0..1" Invoice : has
OrderLine "1" --> "0..1" Delivery : belongs to
Delivery "1" --> "1" Customer : delivered to
Stock "1" --> "0..*" Product : tracks

@enduml

---

### Summary of Key Elements:

| Class        | Purpose                                                                 |
|--------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `Customer`   | Represents a customer with address, VAT number, and orders             |
| `Product`    | Tracks product details and current stock level                         |
| `Order`      | Manages an order with payment and shipping status                      |
| `OrderLine`  | Represents individual items in an order with shipment tracking         |
| `Stock`      | Keeps track of available stock per product                             |
| `Delivery`   | Tracks the state of shipments (packed, shipped, received, damaged)     |
| `Invoice`    | Manages invoicing with payment options and status                      |

This diagram evolves across all steps, including handling partial deliveries, multi-address support, invoice generation, and detailed delivery tracking.

